From Okwe Obi, Abuja A patrol vehicle has been donated to the Neighbourhoods, Estates and Residents Association of Abuja Forum (NERAAF), by a law and consultancy firm, Ezeobi and Partners, to tame criminality. Earlier, NERAAF Chairman, Barr Jude Ezeobi, had urged residents of the FCT to be careful during and after the general elections. Ezeobi, at a press conference recently in Abuja, noted that the association had a situation room to monitor issues as they emerge across the nation’s capital. “Avoid disclosing your address to any stranger especially during and after the ballots. Fix all locks and avoid dropping off keys with other people “Get to know your neigbours so you can identify a stranger in case of an emergency. “Ensure that your home and estate securities observe maximum verification before admitting visitors,” he advised.